include ../components/mixins.pug

section
  +section-head('Modifiers', 'modifiers', 'https://docs.qmk.fm/#/feature_advanced_keycodes?id=modifier-keys')

  .block
    h3 Modifier Keycode Functions

    table
      thead
        tr
          td Keycode #[aside to be added to your call to KEYMAP()]
          td Description
      tbody
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                LSFT(KC_XXXX)
          td applies left Shift to KC_XXXX (keycode) - S(KC_XXXX) is an alias
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                RSFT(KC_XXXX)
          td applies right Shift to KC_XXXX
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                LCTL(KC_XXXX)
          td applies left Control to KC_XXXX
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                RCTL(KC_XXXX)
          td applies right Control to KC_XXXX
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                LALT(KC_XXXX)
          td applies left Alt to KC_XXXX
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                RALT(KC_XXXX)
          td applies right Alt to KC_XXXX
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                LGUI(KC_XXXX)
          td applies left GUI (command/win) to KC_XXXX
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                RGUI(KC_XXXX)
          td applies right GUI (command/win) to KC_XXXX
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                HYPR(KC_XXXX)
          td applies Hyper (all modifiers) to KC_XXXX
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                MEH(KC_XXXX)
          td applies Meh (all modifiers except Win/Cmd) to KC_XXXX
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                LCAG(KC_XXXX)
          td applies CtrlAltGui to KC_XXXX

    p You can also chain these, like this: LALT(LCTL(KC_DEL)) -- this makes a key that sends Alt, Control, and Delete in a single keypress.


  .block
    h3 Modifier Special Functions

    table
      thead
        td Keycode #[aside to be added to your call to KEYMAP()]
        td Description
      tbody
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                MT(MOD_XXXX, KC_XXXX)
          td When held, activate modifier XXXX (see below) #[br] When tapped, send KC_XXXX.
        tr
          td
            pre
              code.language-c.
                OSM(MOD_XXXX)
          td Activate modifier XXXX (see below) for the next key pressed.

    h4 Modifiers
    p You may use any of the following modifiers in the above special functions.
    ul
      li MOD_LCTL
      li MOD_LSFT
      li MOD_LALT
      li MOD_LGUI
      li MOD_RCTL
      li MOD_RSFT
      li MOD_RALT
      li MOD_RGUI
      li MOD_HYPR
      li MOD_MEH